To load ardupilot parameters from file from mavproxy console
param load <path_to_file>/ardu_param_for_gimbal.parm

AS REPORTED IN https://ardupilot.org/dev/docs/using-sitl-for-ardupilot-testing.html:
"This only needs to be done once, after loading, the parameters are stored in the simulated EEPROM"

To save ardupilot parameters to file from mavproxy console (if important changes to be shared have been done)
param save <path_to_file>/ardu_param_for_gimbal.parm


